56
00:01:41,059 --> 00:01:41,601
[GEORGIA FIRES BACK]

57
00:01:43,603 --> 00:01:46,231
[SUGAR VOICEOVER] What is the difference
between the law and karma?

58
00:01:46,648 --> 00:01:48,650
The law punishes.

59
00:01:48,858 --> 00:01:49,901
While karma...

60
00:01:50,652 --> 00:01:51,694
- kills.

61
00:01:57,909 --> 00:01:59,452
Thanks for the update, Inspector.

62
00:02:00,245 --> 00:02:02,122
I’ll tell them the story.

63
00:02:03,414 --> 00:02:04,290
Alright.

64
00:02:08,711 --> 00:02:10,213
Was that Inspector Georgia?

65
00:02:12,006 --> 00:02:14,300
They were able to catch Mr. Leonard Zamora.

66
00:02:15,301 --> 00:02:16,802
There was an encounter.

67
00:02:16,803 --> 00:02:19,347
The two sides fired shots.

68
00:02:22,433 --> 00:02:24,686
Then Mr. Zamora died.

69
00:02:24,978 --> 00:02:26,980
Oh, no.

70
00:02:27,564 --> 00:02:28,647
I’m sorry, Ma’am

71
00:02:28,648 --> 00:02:30,984
[IRENE] I know he wasn’t
the kindest person, but...

72
00:02:32,402 --> 00:02:33,862
- he was my husband.

73
00:02:33,987 --> 00:02:35,738
He’s the father of my child.

74
00:02:36,364 --> 00:02:37,198
And most of all,

75
00:02:37,199 --> 00:02:38,783
I still loved Leonard.

76
00:02:46,416 --> 00:02:47,250
[JURO GRUNTS]

77
00:02:50,879 --> 00:02:51,796
You loved him?

78
00:02:54,132 --> 00:02:57,427
When did you stop loving him?

79
00:02:58,386 --> 00:02:59,636
Was it when you found out?

80
00:02:59,637 --> 00:03:05,518
Never. I didn’t know that
he would become a child abuser.

81
00:03:07,478 --> 00:03:10,607
He had a lot of friends
the same age as he was.

82
00:03:11,441 --> 00:03:13,401
But I thought it was just that.

83
00:03:15,361 --> 00:03:17,322
He really was sneaky.

84
00:03:17,864 --> 00:03:20,491
Had I known that he would be like that,

85
00:03:21,868 --> 00:03:24,244
I wouldn’t have left Zach under his care.

86
00:03:24,245 --> 00:03:26,039
I should’ve run away with Zach.

87
00:03:27,498 --> 00:03:30,375
I left Zach under his care
because he has the financial capability.

88
00:03:30,376 --> 00:03:32,586
I thought he would give
Zach a good life,

89
00:03:32,587 --> 00:03:34,172
but I was wrong.

90
00:03:36,925 --> 00:03:40,094
Aunt, stop blaming yourself.

91
00:03:41,429 --> 00:03:43,181
We were all fooled by Uncle Leonard.

92
00:03:49,479 --> 00:03:50,480
Partner,

93
00:03:52,732 --> 00:03:54,525
I have something to ask you.

94
00:03:55,318 --> 00:03:59,989
Did you really only remember
everything now?

95
00:04:02,492 --> 00:04:06,579
You really had no recollection of
everything he did to you?

96
00:04:15,171 --> 00:04:17,090
How did that happen? Amnesia?

97
00:04:19,467 --> 00:04:28,893
[GEMINI BY JULIE ANNE SAN JOSE PLAYING]

98
00:04:59,090 --> 00:05:00,383
Nurse, nurse.

99
00:05:01,467 --> 00:05:03,010
Do you have an update
on my dad’s case?

100
00:05:03,011 --> 00:05:04,554
He’s Charlie Chua.

101
00:05:05,221 --> 00:05:06,847
They’re still in there, Ma’am.

102
00:05:06,848 --> 00:05:07,807
Kindly wait for the doctor,

103
00:05:07,808 --> 00:05:09,349
and he’ll give an update later.

104
00:05:09,350 --> 00:05:10,684
We’ve been waiting for a long time,

105
00:05:10,685 --> 00:05:13,521
and nobody has told me
anything about my dad.

106
00:05:14,022 --> 00:05:17,899
Can’t you just try phoning them
so you’ll have an update?

107
00:05:17,900 --> 00:05:18,443
Alright. One moment.

108
00:05:18,444 --> 00:05:20,110
- Let me assist here.
- Please call them now.

109
00:05:20,111 --> 00:05:22,446
I want to know now what
happened to my dad.

110
00:05:22,447 --> 00:05:23,323
Yana. Just calm down.

111
00:05:24,907 --> 00:05:25,783
Yana. Just calm down,

112
00:05:25,784 --> 00:05:27,243
the nurses are becoming frantic.

113
00:05:28,703 --> 00:05:30,413
Don’t worry, the doctors here are good.

114
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:31,956
Your dad will be okay.

115
00:05:31,957 --> 00:05:33,041
Uncle will survive.

116
00:05:33,624 --> 00:05:35,835
Gabo, I can’t lose him right now.

117
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:40,006
Gabo, Dad promised to be better.

118
00:05:40,465 --> 00:05:42,007
He said he will change for the better.

119
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:43,175
I can’t lose him right now.

120
00:05:43,176 --> 00:05:45,136
I can’t lose him right now.

121
00:05:52,894 --> 00:05:55,396
It is called dissociative amnesia.

122
00:05:55,605 --> 00:05:58,357
Not to confuse it with the kind
of amnesia everybody knows.

123
00:05:58,358 --> 00:06:01,152
It isn’t like you bumped your head
and lost your memories.

124
00:06:02,070 --> 00:06:05,531
Uncle Leonard said he would
mix my drinks with drugs.

125
00:06:05,948 --> 00:06:06,866
Yes.

126
00:06:06,867 --> 00:06:09,284
Certain types of drugs
and alcohol can make people

127
00:06:09,285 --> 00:06:12,079
forget their bad memories.

128
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:13,080
What happened to you,

129
00:06:13,081 --> 00:06:14,206
what you experienced,

130
00:06:14,207 --> 00:06:16,666
was a trauma response.

131
00:06:16,667 --> 00:06:21,005
It’s your brain’s defense mechanism
to erase bad memories.

132
00:06:22,006 --> 00:06:25,551
But when I saw the photo
of the American man,

133
00:06:25,885 --> 00:06:28,012
I suddenly remembered some memories.

134
00:06:28,638 --> 00:06:29,846
Yes.

135
00:06:29,847 --> 00:06:34,643
No matter how much
we bury our dark memories,

136
00:06:34,644 --> 00:06:37,604
they will come back when
it’s triggered by what

137
00:06:37,605 --> 00:06:39,773
we see or smell.

138
00:06:39,774 --> 00:06:41,067
Like what they say,

139
00:06:41,442 --> 00:06:43,485
the mind may forget,

140
00:06:43,486 --> 00:06:45,196
but the body remembers.

141
00:06:46,531 --> 00:06:48,491
Is it possible for me to
recall my memories?

142
00:06:49,450 --> 00:06:51,577
I want to remember as much as I can.

143
00:06:51,953 --> 00:06:56,958
So I can remember the people
who did us wrong and abused us.

144
00:06:57,625 --> 00:06:59,836
So we can stop them.

145
00:07:00,878 --> 00:07:04,215
There is a way to recover
these buried memories...

146
00:07:04,757 --> 00:07:06,050
Through therapy.

147
00:07:09,846 --> 00:07:11,096
[PHONE RINGING]

148
00:07:11,097 --> 00:07:14,308
[CRIES AND SOBS]

149
00:07:14,976 --> 00:07:16,227
Hello, Mom.

150
00:07:16,519 --> 00:07:20,440
Mom, I’m still here at the hospital.

151
00:07:21,065 --> 00:07:21,732
Don’t worry,

152
00:07:21,732 --> 00:07:22,358
[LIV CATCHING HER BREATH]

153
00:07:22,358 --> 00:07:22,984
I’m-

154
00:07:22,985 --> 00:07:24,360
I’m safe.

155
00:07:24,944 --> 00:07:26,987
[CRIES AND SOBS]

156
00:07:26,988 --> 00:07:29,740
There’s no update yet
regarding Uncle Charlie.

157
00:07:32,535 --> 00:07:33,494
Alright, Mom.

158
00:07:33,495 --> 00:07:34,996
Let’s talk later.

159
00:07:36,789 --> 00:07:37,457
Okay, bye.

160
00:07:39,542 --> 00:07:43,171
[WATER RUNNING]

161
00:08:06,027 --> 00:08:07,528
[LIV STARTS SHAKING]

162
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:17,622
Sugar.

163
00:08:18,122 --> 00:08:18,873
Yana.

164
00:08:19,457 --> 00:08:20,833
You can go home for a while.

165
00:08:22,919 --> 00:08:23,753
Thank you.

166
00:08:23,754 --> 00:08:25,087
What is she still doing here?

167
00:08:26,756 --> 00:08:28,006
What do you mean?

168
00:08:28,007 --> 00:08:30,467
Of course, I’m here to watch over you.

169
00:08:30,468 --> 00:08:32,303
I don’t care, okay?

170
00:08:32,845 --> 00:08:34,471
I don’t want to see you again.

171
00:08:34,472 --> 00:08:36,515
Yana, Sugar is just
looking out for you.

172
00:08:36,516 --> 00:08:38,142
I don’t care!

173
00:08:39,143 --> 00:08:39,894
Yana.

174
00:08:39,895 --> 00:08:42,313
She is the reason
why Dad got shot!

175
00:08:46,984 --> 00:08:48,443
There’s an emergency in room 1109.

176
00:08:48,444 --> 00:08:49,946
Please page the doctor!

177
00:08:50,947 --> 00:08:51,781
Wait, that’s my dad’s room.

178
00:08:52,698 --> 00:08:53,907
Nurse, is my dad okay?

179
00:08:53,908 --> 00:08:54,700
Wait a minute.

180
00:08:54,701 --> 00:08:55,701
What’s the emergency?

181
00:08:55,702 --> 00:08:57,620
Can you please tell me
what’s happening?

182
00:08:57,870 --> 00:08:58,704
One moment, Ma’am.

183
00:08:58,913 --> 00:09:00,497
Can you please just tell me something?

184
00:09:00,498 --> 00:09:01,665
I will sue all of you.

185
00:09:01,666 --> 00:09:03,416
Would you like me to file
a case of medical malpractice?

186
00:09:03,417 --> 00:09:04,751
Or negligence?

187
00:09:04,752 --> 00:09:05,835
- Yana. Calm down first.
- Can you just please tell me...

188
00:09:05,836 --> 00:09:07,421
Something already?
Come on!

189
00:09:07,672 --> 00:09:08,256
[SUGAR] Yana.

190
00:09:08,257 --> 00:09:10,424
Let them do their jobs.

191
00:09:10,758 --> 00:09:11,884
- Yana.
- Dad.

192
00:09:12,176 --> 00:09:13,010
Yana!

193
00:09:18,140 --> 00:09:19,392
[GEORGIA] Mrs. Zamora,

194
00:09:20,643 --> 00:09:22,061
my condolences.

195
00:09:23,854 --> 00:09:25,355
We apologize for the inconvenience.

196
00:09:25,356 --> 00:09:27,650
We just really need
to have this interview.

197
00:09:28,484 --> 00:09:31,237
So you can be sure that
I did not kill Zach?

198
00:09:36,450 --> 00:09:38,077
It’s okay, Inspector.

199
00:09:38,661 --> 00:09:42,248
Inspector Kirby already
briefed me about this.

200
00:09:46,544 --> 00:09:48,462
Why did you just show up now?

201
00:09:49,672 --> 00:09:53,217
You did not even go to
the wake of your son.

202
00:09:56,470 --> 00:09:58,306
I was trying to stay away from Leonard.

203
00:09:58,723 --> 00:10:04,186
But I already gave
my statement to Juro...

204
00:10:05,771 --> 00:10:07,440
- about my son’s death.

205
00:10:08,608 --> 00:10:10,318
Yes, we read that statement.

206
00:10:11,402 --> 00:10:13,446
We didn’t see anything wrong.

207
00:10:14,447 --> 00:10:18,284
I was told that you’re
already based in Hong Kong.

208
00:10:19,285 --> 00:10:22,371
I have been working there
ever since Leonard and I separated.

209
00:10:23,664 --> 00:10:25,291
I didn’t want to see him again.

210
00:10:25,791 --> 00:10:29,253
But I wanted to see my son.

211
00:10:30,004 --> 00:10:32,340
I wanted to see him even from afar.

212
00:10:34,759 --> 00:10:36,427
I would take photos of him.

213
00:10:38,679 --> 00:10:40,640
I would watch him from a distance.

214
00:10:42,350 --> 00:10:46,103
But I never approached him to talk.

215
00:10:47,396 --> 00:10:49,440
Until recently.

216
00:11:40,908 --> 00:11:42,243
What are you doing here?

217
00:11:44,787 --> 00:11:45,788
My son.

218
00:11:48,541 --> 00:11:49,792
Your son?

219
00:11:51,460 --> 00:11:53,337
Stop calling me that.

220
00:11:54,839 --> 00:11:55,964
I stopped being your son

221
00:11:55,965 --> 00:11:57,341
the day you left.

222
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:02,513
[MAN] Sir.

223
00:12:05,182 --> 00:12:06,599
Let’s not talk here.

224
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:07,893
Follow me.

225
00:12:14,692 --> 00:12:15,776
Zach.

226
00:12:16,652 --> 00:12:18,195
Zach, let’s talk.

227
00:12:24,785 --> 00:12:26,035
Pancake.

228
00:12:26,036 --> 00:12:27,496
Do you remember that?

229
00:12:28,831 --> 00:12:30,875
You left me with a pancake.

230
00:12:31,375 --> 00:12:34,503
After cooking breakfast, you left.

231
00:12:35,629 --> 00:12:37,213
No explanation.

232
00:12:37,214 --> 00:12:38,257
No texts.

233
00:12:38,883 --> 00:12:39,550
Nothing.

234
00:12:41,927 --> 00:12:43,512
I’m sorry, dear.

235
00:12:44,764 --> 00:12:48,309
I couldn’t take your
father’s infidelity anymore.

236
00:12:51,479 --> 00:12:52,772
What about me?

237
00:12:54,857 --> 00:12:56,692
I was eight years old.

238
00:12:59,111 --> 00:13:01,113
I can’t even tie my own shoelaces.

239
00:13:03,324 --> 00:13:05,034
I needed my mother.

240
00:13:12,124 --> 00:13:13,959
Zach, I couldn’t do it.

241
00:13:14,627 --> 00:13:18,672
I couldn’t do it because
I didn’t have my own job.

242
00:13:19,757 --> 00:13:22,050
I didn’t have the money to raise you.

243
00:13:22,051 --> 00:13:27,223
But Leonard could give you a better life.

244
00:13:27,515 --> 00:13:29,809
Well, that didn’t happen!

245
00:13:32,353 --> 00:13:33,771
That is not what happened.

246
00:13:35,523 --> 00:13:38,692
What happened to me is nothing
like what you’re thinking!

247
00:13:41,237 --> 00:13:42,905
My gym?

248
00:13:46,492 --> 00:13:47,535
Everything...

249
00:13:47,785 --> 00:13:49,328
is just an act.

250
00:13:51,914 --> 00:13:53,374
But deep inside...

251
00:13:55,459 --> 00:13:56,460
Deep inside,

252
00:13:57,753 --> 00:13:59,088
I’m rotten.

253
00:13:59,171 --> 00:14:00,214
[IRENE SOBS]

254
00:14:02,007 --> 00:14:03,050
[ZACH SOBS]

255
00:14:03,801 --> 00:14:05,427
I’m damaged.

256
00:14:06,554 --> 00:14:07,596
[IRENE SOBS]

257
00:14:08,973 --> 00:14:11,350
And it’s all because of you!

258
00:14:12,142 --> 00:14:13,185
[ZACH SOBS]

259
00:14:13,227 --> 00:14:15,020
It’s because of you!

260
00:14:15,271 --> 00:14:16,313
[IRENE SOBS]

261
00:14:16,689 --> 00:14:19,400
- Forgive me.
- Because you left me!

262
00:14:20,609 --> 00:14:21,652
[ZACH SCOFFS]

263
00:14:23,237 --> 00:14:25,405
Zach, I’m sorry.

264
00:14:25,406 --> 00:14:26,615
You know what, Irene?

265
00:14:27,241 --> 00:14:29,451
I had to fend for myself.

266
00:14:30,494 --> 00:14:33,581
I had to fight every monster alone!

267
00:14:34,707 --> 00:14:37,293
[ZACH SOBS]

268
00:14:37,793 --> 00:14:40,462
Because you left me!

269
00:14:41,213 --> 00:14:42,256
[IRENE SOBS]

270
00:14:43,215 --> 00:14:44,591
Forgive me, Zach.

271
00:14:44,592 --> 00:14:45,675
If only I had known.

272
00:14:45,676 --> 00:14:48,344
If I had known, I wouldn’t have
left you with Leonard.

273
00:14:48,345 --> 00:14:49,263
It’s too late.

274
00:14:50,097 --> 00:14:51,724
It’s too late now, Irene.

275
00:14:54,518 --> 00:14:56,645
You can’t reverse who I am.

276
00:15:00,983 --> 00:15:02,943
I hope you’re happy.

277
00:15:05,195 --> 00:15:06,363
[IRENE SOBS]

278
00:15:09,617 --> 00:15:10,075
[ZACH SOBS]

279
00:15:11,076 --> 00:15:12,453
Just leave!

280
00:15:13,370 --> 00:15:14,204
[IRENE SOBS]

281
00:15:16,498 --> 00:15:17,124
[ZACH SCOFFS]

282
00:15:23,297 --> 00:15:26,800
And that was the last time
I saw my son alive!

283
00:15:28,135 --> 00:15:31,388
He was trying to refill
his bottle of water to drink.

284
00:15:32,473 --> 00:15:35,809
To replace all the tears
he lost because of me.

285
00:15:37,311 --> 00:15:39,771
So Zach was drinking water then?

286
00:15:39,772 --> 00:15:42,148
I didn’t see any eye drops
in the crime scene,

287
00:15:42,149 --> 00:15:43,484
or even in Zach’s office!

288
00:15:43,651 --> 00:15:45,361
We still have Zach’s water bottle.

289
00:15:45,444 --> 00:15:47,153
It’s contents haven’t been tested yet.

290
00:15:47,154 --> 00:15:48,822
We’ll have it done
as soon as possible!

291
00:15:50,491 --> 00:15:51,951
He was indeed poisoned.

292
00:15:52,242 --> 00:15:56,412
If he wasn’t poisoned he
could’ve survived his burns.

293
00:15:56,413 --> 00:15:59,958
Poisoning is the real cause
of Zach Zamora’s death.

294
00:15:59,959 --> 00:16:04,505
Whoever put the eye drops in Zach’s
water bottle which led to his death,

295
00:16:05,005 --> 00:16:07,299
they’re the real killer.

296
00:16:10,010 --> 00:16:10,636
[IRENE STUTTERS]

297
00:16:10,637 --> 00:16:13,305
He took water from
the water dispenser.

298
00:16:13,722 --> 00:16:14,348
[IRENE SOBS]

299
00:16:15,224 --> 00:16:18,977
Did you notice anything
different about his drink?

300
00:16:18,978 --> 00:16:19,603
[IRENE SOBS]

301
00:16:20,729 --> 00:16:21,313
Nothing.

302
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:22,147
Nothing.

303
00:16:41,458 --> 00:16:43,167
[YANA SOBS]

304
00:16:43,168 --> 00:16:44,211
Miss Chua.

305
00:16:45,212 --> 00:16:47,589
I’m so sorry to say this to you.

306
00:16:48,882 --> 00:16:51,552
Your father suffered cardiac arrest.

307
00:16:51,802 --> 00:16:53,720
And despite our efforts

308
00:16:53,721 --> 00:16:57,891
to resuscitate him, his heart stopped,

309
00:16:58,308 --> 00:17:00,102
and we were unable to revive him.

310
00:17:00,686 --> 00:17:01,562
I’m so sorry, Miss Chua.

311
00:17:01,563 --> 00:17:08,569
No, no, no, no.
[YANA SOBS]

312
00:17:10,946 --> 00:17:14,241
[YANA WAILING]

313
00:17:17,745 --> 00:17:23,792
Daddy, wake up! No!

314
00:17:24,501 --> 00:17:28,504
[YANA CRIES]

315
00:17:28,505 --> 00:17:29,839
Daddy.

316
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:33,426
You said you’d change.
Why did you leave me?

317
00:17:33,427 --> 00:17:36,096
Daddy!

318
00:17:36,472 --> 00:17:41,768
Daddy, you can’t leave me!

319
00:17:41,769 --> 00:17:44,855
[YANA CRIES]

320
00:17:46,732 --> 00:17:49,735
Daddy. Wake up.

321
00:17:56,158 --> 00:17:57,408
I don’t know what to say.

322
00:17:57,409 --> 00:18:03,290
[YANA CRIES]

323
00:18:03,665 --> 00:18:06,959
- [GABO] Just always remember that we are here.
- [YANA CRIES]

324
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:08,377
- I am here for you.
- [YANA CRIES]

325
00:18:08,378 --> 00:18:11,756
[YANA CRIES]

326
00:18:11,757 --> 00:18:13,133
I’ll always be here, Yana.

327
00:18:13,175 --> 00:18:15,552
[YANA CRIES]

328
00:18:15,969 --> 00:18:21,100
[YANA SOBS]

329
00:18:21,767 --> 00:18:25,896
[YANA CRIES]

330
00:18:26,063 --> 00:18:31,652
Yana, it’s hard to lose someone you love.

331
00:18:33,237 --> 00:18:34,571
[YANA SOBS]

332
00:18:34,863 --> 00:18:37,407
I know because I went through the same thing.

333
00:18:37,449 --> 00:18:39,701
[YANA SOBS]

334
00:18:41,078 --> 00:18:42,703
It will never be easy.

335
00:18:42,704 --> 00:18:43,705
- But...
- [YANA SOBS]

336
00:18:46,875 --> 00:18:49,878
the pain will also stay.

337
00:18:50,921 --> 00:18:55,758
Someday, you will
just get used to it.

338
00:18:55,759 --> 00:18:57,009
You will get used to the pain.

339
00:18:57,010 --> 00:18:58,554
We’ll be with you-

340
00:18:59,388 --> 00:19:01,056
Really? Huh?

341
00:19:01,431 --> 00:19:02,558
Really?
Coming from you?

342
00:19:02,766 --> 00:19:03,684
Coming from you?

343
00:19:03,725 --> 00:19:05,519
- Coming from you, Sugar?
- Why?

344
00:19:05,561 --> 00:19:05,894
Huh?

345
00:19:05,895 --> 00:19:06,936
- Why are you -
- [YANA SOBS]

346
00:19:06,937 --> 00:19:08,146
I don’t need your opinion.

347
00:19:08,147 --> 00:19:09,397
I don’t need your love.

348
00:19:09,398 --> 00:19:11,066
I don’t need your sympathy!

349
00:19:11,150 --> 00:19:12,067
[GABO] Yana.

350
00:19:12,401 --> 00:19:14,278
- Yana, that’s too much.
- [SUGAR] Why are you mad at me?

351
00:19:15,612 --> 00:19:17,238
This just feels right.

352
00:19:17,239 --> 00:19:20,074
Because of you, here we are.

353
00:19:20,075 --> 00:19:23,327
Because of you, my dad is dead.

354
00:19:23,328 --> 00:19:24,412
[YANA CRIES]

355
00:19:24,413 --> 00:19:25,788
Why are you blaming it on me?

356
00:19:25,789 --> 00:19:26,290
Wait.

357
00:19:26,291 --> 00:19:27,373
Why me?

358
00:19:27,374 --> 00:19:28,749
Yana, why blame me?

359
00:19:28,750 --> 00:19:30,585
It was Leonard who shot your dad.

360
00:19:30,586 --> 00:19:31,586
It wasn’t me.

361
00:19:31,587 --> 00:19:35,882
Sugar. We almost escaped.
We were there already.

362
00:19:35,883 --> 00:19:38,050
My dad was supposed
to help us escape.

363
00:19:38,051 --> 00:19:40,345
But because of you-

364
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:42,930
Because of you-

365
00:19:42,931 --> 00:19:44,891
Because of you,
you still went back!

366
00:19:44,892 --> 00:19:45,726
Wait.

367
00:19:45,727 --> 00:19:47,768
You know that we left Liv behind.

368
00:19:47,769 --> 00:19:49,729
- I couldn’t leave her behind.
- Oh my God.

369
00:19:49,730 --> 00:19:51,147
I had to get to her.

370
00:19:51,148 --> 00:19:53,858
That’s the reason why
Uncle Leonard heard us

371
00:19:53,859 --> 00:19:55,568
and we got hurt!

372
00:19:55,569 --> 00:19:57,486
If you only waited.

373
00:19:57,487 --> 00:20:01,365
If you had only waited
for a few moments,

374
00:20:01,366 --> 00:20:06,120
we could have strategized
how to escape properly.

375
00:20:06,121 --> 00:20:08,498
We wouldn’t be here
if it weren’t for that.

376
00:20:09,124 --> 00:20:10,124
[YANA CRIES]

377
00:20:10,125 --> 00:20:11,125
[GABO] Stop it, Yana.

378
00:20:11,126 --> 00:20:13,502
You killed my father!

379
00:20:13,503 --> 00:20:14,962
That’s not true.

380
00:20:14,963 --> 00:20:16,339
Come on.

381
00:20:16,340 --> 00:20:17,548
That’s not true.

382
00:20:17,549 --> 00:20:19,217
You get out of here!

383
00:20:19,218 --> 00:20:20,384
I don’t want to see you.

384
00:20:20,385 --> 00:20:22,762
I never want to see your face again!

385
00:20:22,763 --> 00:20:24,013
You get out!

386
00:20:24,014 --> 00:20:25,849
[SUGAR CRIES]

387
00:20:27,142 --> 00:20:31,687
[YANA CRIES]

388
00:20:31,688 --> 00:20:32,856
Daddy.

389
00:20:33,357 --> 00:20:34,357
[YANA CRIES]

390
00:20:34,358 --> 00:20:38,986
[YANA WAILS]

391
00:20:38,987 --> 00:20:41,281
Daddy!

392
00:20:49,122 --> 00:20:50,874
I’m sorry, it’s the only
thing I could afford.

393
00:20:51,541 --> 00:20:52,708
Please eat.

394
00:20:52,709 --> 00:20:54,503
You haven’t eaten since last night.

395
00:21:00,592 --> 00:21:04,554
They already took my dad
to the funeral parlor.

396
00:21:06,932 --> 00:21:09,685
I gave them permission to
cremate dad’s body.

397
00:21:12,062 --> 00:21:14,314
Nobody will visit him anyway.

398
00:21:15,107 --> 00:21:17,484
I’m his only family left.

399
00:21:17,901 --> 00:21:20,279
By the way, Liv texted.

400
00:21:21,071 --> 00:21:23,782
She’s coming with her family.

401
00:21:26,702 --> 00:21:29,121
Have you talked to Sugar yet?

402
00:21:32,207 --> 00:21:34,001
Why would I talk to that woman?

403
00:21:35,460 --> 00:21:36,962
Are you still blaming her?

404
00:21:37,754 --> 00:21:39,589
It was an accident, Yana.

405
00:21:40,924 --> 00:21:42,800
She didn’t want
Uncle Charlie to get shot.

406
00:21:42,801 --> 00:21:43,885
Really?

407
00:21:44,428 --> 00:21:44,970
Hmm?

408
00:21:45,679 --> 00:21:47,514
Really? You’re siding with her?

409
00:21:48,390 --> 00:21:49,141
Huh?

410
00:21:49,933 --> 00:21:51,892
You’re taking that woman’s side?

411
00:21:51,893 --> 00:21:54,563
Because I know you’re just
looking for someone to blame.

412
00:21:55,439 --> 00:21:57,399
I know you’re grieving, Yana.

413
00:21:57,691 --> 00:21:59,359
Everyone would feel the same.

414
00:21:59,985 --> 00:22:02,779
But you shouldn’t pin
the blame on Sugar.

415
00:22:05,407 --> 00:22:07,242
Who should I be mad at?

416
00:22:10,162 --> 00:22:11,455
At Uncle Leonard?

417
00:22:13,749 --> 00:22:15,000
Gaboi, he’s dead.

418
00:22:17,419 --> 00:22:18,670
Towards Zach?

419
00:22:21,089 --> 00:22:22,341
He’s also dead.

420
00:22:23,258 --> 00:22:24,051
So tell me.

421
00:22:24,051 --> 00:22:24,885
Who should I be mad at?

422
00:22:24,885 --> 00:22:25,427
[YANA SNIFFLES]

423
00:22:27,262 --> 00:22:27,804
[YANA SNIFFLES]

424
00:22:27,805 --> 00:22:32,434
To whom should I air out all of my
frustrations now that Dad’s gone?

425
00:22:32,976 --> 00:22:34,478
Yana, I don’t know.
But...

426
00:22:36,146 --> 00:22:38,440
But what I know is
Sugar isn’t your enemy.

427
00:22:38,523 --> 00:22:40,484
You keep saying Sugar’s name.
Just be with her instead.

428
00:22:40,567 --> 00:22:41,443
[GABO GRUNTS]

429
00:22:41,651 --> 00:22:42,569
[GABO GRUNTS]

430
00:22:47,741 --> 00:22:48,700
Yana!

431
00:22:49,326 --> 00:22:51,160
You didn’t have to pick me up.

432
00:22:51,161 --> 00:22:52,871
Kirby could’ve just driven me home.

433
00:22:53,288 --> 00:22:54,830
That’s fine.

434
00:22:54,831 --> 00:22:57,167
It somehow makes me feel better.

435
00:22:57,417 --> 00:22:59,753
As if I’m doing this for Zach.

436
00:23:00,212 --> 00:23:01,797
So where’s Yana?

437
00:23:02,464 --> 00:23:04,256
I’ve been calling her,
but she isn’t answering.

438
00:23:04,257 --> 00:23:05,842
Try to phone Gabo instead.

439
00:23:09,221 --> 00:23:10,097
Uhmm..

440
00:23:10,514 --> 00:23:11,264
Liv.

441
00:23:11,598 --> 00:23:12,474
Sir Hector.

442
00:23:15,727 --> 00:23:16,395
Inspector.

443
00:23:16,395 --> 00:23:16,895
I’m -

444
00:23:16,895 --> 00:23:17,437
[LIV EXHALES]

445
00:23:17,438 --> 00:23:18,688
I’m glad you’re okay.

446
00:23:20,357 --> 00:23:22,316
My wound isn’t that deep.

447
00:23:22,317 --> 00:23:24,861
So the doctor discharged me immediately.

448
00:23:26,696 --> 00:23:27,572
[JURO] Uhh...

449
00:23:28,365 --> 00:23:31,034
Aunt, this is Liv.

450
00:23:31,660 --> 00:23:32,702
Zach’s ex-girlfriend.

451
00:23:33,370 --> 00:23:36,039
Liv, this is Aunt Irene.

452
00:23:36,373 --> 00:23:37,624
She’s Zach’s Mom.

453
00:23:40,961 --> 00:23:43,505
I would see her in Zach’s posts.

454
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:47,551
I’m Hector.

455
00:23:49,094 --> 00:23:50,137
Liv’s father.

456
00:23:53,098 --> 00:23:54,558
I think I remember you.

457
00:23:56,852 --> 00:23:58,687
We seen each other before.

458
00:24:23,628 --> 00:24:24,754
For my eyes.

459
00:24:28,091 --> 00:24:29,885
In Zach’s office.

460
00:24:30,677 --> 00:24:32,596
The day he died.

461
00:24:34,389 --> 00:24:36,015
Dad, is that true?

462
00:24:36,016 --> 00:24:37,058
Yes.

463
00:24:38,226 --> 00:24:39,769
You were holding something.

464
00:24:40,770 --> 00:24:41,938
I think...

465
00:24:42,230 --> 00:24:43,523
I think it was eye drops.

466
00:24:45,317 --> 00:24:47,027
Are you sure of what you saw?

467
00:24:48,195 --> 00:24:49,070
Yes.

468
00:24:49,863 --> 00:24:52,240
Because after Zach and I talked,

469
00:24:52,532 --> 00:24:54,492
I returned to Zach’s office.

470
00:24:54,493 --> 00:24:55,494
Him.

471
00:24:55,702 --> 00:24:56,870
It was him!

472
00:24:57,162 --> 00:24:59,163
He’s the one I saw.

473
00:24:59,164 --> 00:25:00,916
He was holding some eye drops.

474
00:25:01,917 --> 00:25:04,711
[SUGAR VOICEOVER]
The law and karma are partners.

475
00:25:05,003 --> 00:25:07,589
If you don’t get punished
by the law,

476
00:25:07,797 --> 00:25:10,008
then karma will
be coming for you.

477
00:25:11,551 --> 00:25:14,179
You were right to tell me
what you discovered.

478
00:25:15,055 --> 00:25:17,098
But before we report it,

479
00:25:17,682 --> 00:25:20,936
we need new evidence to reopen the case.

480
00:25:21,228 --> 00:25:23,980
One of the four friends.

481
00:25:27,901 --> 00:25:28,735
Yana!

482
00:25:30,195 --> 00:25:34,281
The eyedrop that was used to poison Zach
is the same brand as the

483
00:25:34,282 --> 00:25:35,742
company where Liv works.

484
00:25:36,576 --> 00:25:38,495
It’s possible that Liv
gave him the eye drops.

485
00:25:38,745 --> 00:25:41,623
This would be the method
that Mr. Baltazar used.

486
00:25:41,873 --> 00:25:43,999
We found our potential killer!

487
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:47,127
The court will not give an arrest order

488
00:25:47,128 --> 00:25:51,007
if we aren’t able to give
a tight and solid evidence.
